Kitahara Sayaka is a Japanese singer, actress and voice actress born on November 29, 1993 in Saitama Prefecture, Japan.

Sayaka was a member of Hello Pro Egg, under Hello! Project from 2004 to 2011, starring during this time the anime Kirarin Revolution as Noel Yukino and part of the unit MilkyWay (a tie-in with the anime). She graduated in 2011 and began a solo career as voice actress and singer, starring as Aoi Sorano on Inazuma Eleven GO and singing the first ending of the anime, Yappa Seishun (tr. It’s Gotta Be Youth).

Aoi Yabusaki, better known by her stage name Aoi Yuuki, is a Japanese actress, voice actress and singer represented by Pro-Fit.

Yuuki entered the entertainment industry at the age of four. As a child, she acted in films and dramas. From 1999 to 2002, she made regular appearances on the variety shows Appare Sanma Dai-sensei and Yappari Sanma Dai-sensei which aired on Fuji TV. When she was in fifth grade, she made her debut as a voice actress as [Sakura](https://anilist.co/character/15429/) on [Kino's Journey](https://anilist.co/anime/486/).

In late 2006, she was affiliated with the theater company Central. After her admission to high school in August 2007, she joined the agency Breath, whilst changing her stage name to Aoi Yuuki. In 2008, she got her first major role in [Kure-nai](https://anilist.co/anime/3358/) as [Murasaki Kuhouin](https://anilist.co/character/10174/). In August of the same year, she moved to the agency Pro-Fit.

In October 2011, she won the Newtype award for best lead voice actress for her role as [Madoka Kaname](https://anilist.co/character/37832/) in [Puella Magi Madoka Magica](https://anilist.co/anime/9756/). She was also awarded for Best Lead Actress in the 6th Seiyuu Awards for Madoka Kaname, [Victorique de Blois](https://anilist.co/character/20170/) and [Tooru Ichii](https://anilist.co/character/38904/).

In 2013, Yuuki and [Ayana Taketatsu](https://anilist.co/staff/101996/) formed the singing unit [petit milady](https://anilist.co/staff/116523).

A video game designer. Started his career as a programmer in the late '80s, and later took on roles in writing, designing, directing and producing. In 1998, he founded Level-5, a Japanese video game studio, where he remains its president and CEO.

Known for titles such as Dark Cloud, Dark Chronicle, Inazuma Eleven and Professor Layton.

A Japanese pop group under the "FRAME" label; a joint venture of Level-5, currently with Avex Group and formerly with the Up-Front Group.

They actually debuted on UFG imprint "hachama".  

Current squad: 

- Ton-Nino (Lead vocalist) Elder brother of Hiroshi Dot. 
- KMC (Rapper) - In-Chiquita (Dancer and Choreographer) 
- Hiroshi Dot (Side Vocalist and Dancer) Younger brother of Ton-Nino.

__[Twitter](https://twitter.com/udagaway)__ __Takahiro Udagawa__ is a Japanese script/screenwriter. He is a writer both for the anime industry, and the game industry. In the anime industry he's mostly renowned for working on scripts for sports-themed shows, namely the Ace of Diamond series.
